00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:41.870
And the last one is simply lack of proper
nutrition.

00:00:41.870 --> 00:00:46.590
The first thing you got to understand is that
strength plus quickness equals explosion (strength

00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:48.900
+ quickness = explosion).

00:00:48.900 --> 00:00:54.350
When strength and quickness are applied during
the same muscle contraction, explosion is

00:00:54.350 --> 00:00:55.760
the result.

00:00:55.760 --> 00:01:00.820
You have to maximize your muscle strength
and you have to maximize your muscle quickness

00:01:00.820 --> 00:01:04.190
and neurological response to create that explosion.

00:01:04.190 --> 00:01:07.700
Now: endurance versus explosion.

00:01:07.700 --> 00:01:10.219
Training your jump explosion is counter-intuitive.

00:01:10.219 --> 00:01:13.380
You go out there and you jump for an hour,
working very hard.

00:01:13.380 --> 00:01:17.829
You are sweating, training hard, you feel
the burn and you think you are training correctly.

00:01:17.829 --> 00:01:19.090
Most of you are not.

00:01:19.090 --> 00:01:21.820
You have to train in what is called the improvement
zone.

00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:26.830
If your maximum vertical jump is 32 inches,
and most of your training is done jumping

00:01:26.830 --> 00:01:33.889
at a 12 inch intensity, you are training yourself
to jump 12 inches over a long period of time.

00:01:33.889 --> 00:01:36.240
You are training your jumping endurance.

00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:40.350
This is all about the quality over the quantity.

00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:41.389
Let me give you another example.

00:01:41.389 --> 00:01:45.529
If you were a sprinter training for the 100
meter dash and your coach says you have to

00:01:45.529 --> 00:01:49.640
run 2 miles everyday and it is going to train
you for that 100 meter dash.

00:01:49.640 --> 00:01:52.789
After that workout you are going to be tired,
you are going to be sweaty and you are going

00:01:52.789 --> 00:01:55.350
to be training your jump endurance.

00:01:55.350 --> 00:02:00.939
No sprinter is going to train by running the
mile or 2 mile to run the 100 meter dash.

00:02:00.939 --> 00:02:03.939
You will be training the wrong type of muscle
fiber.

00:02:03.939 --> 00:02:07.959
So as long as you keep training your endurance,
you are not going to be training the right

00:02:07.959 --> 00:02:09.780
type of fast twitch muscle fiber.

